__commit_message__ = 'fix: auto-move inaccessible files (HTTP 400) from tracked_files to skipped_files\n\nWhen get_file_meta returns HTTP 400, the file is permanently inaccessible\nto this API token. Previously, pull would log "no access" and skip it on\nevery run without ever recording that the file is restricted.\n\nNow: pull_file sets no_access=True on PullResult; pull.py detects this,\nmoves the file key from tracked_files to skipped_files (with reason), and\nremoves it from tracked_files. Subsequent runs see it in skipped_files and\nskip the API call entirely. Auto-discovery also respects skipped_files so\nthe file is never re-added.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>'
